text.section:
A qualified domestic relations order shall not:
Require the retirement system to take any action not authorized under state or federal law;
Require the retirement system to provide any benefit, allowance, or other payment not authorized under state or federal law;
Grant or be construed to grant the alternate payee any separate right, title, or interest in or to any retirement benefit other than to receive payments from the participant's account in accordance with the administrative regulations promulgated by the retirement system and as provided by subsections (3) to (11) of this section; or
Grant any separate interest to any person other than the participant.
